{
  "stem": "26465.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And out there, I see it was a very-- just rather muddy day-- it was raining at that time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was in November.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they-- there I see this procession of people being escorted by this gestapo or whatever-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At that time, I didn't know what-- what unit he belonged to, or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was amazed to see-- about, I don't know, there was about 200 people or more-- carrying all kinds of things, and packages, and suitcases, and so on, and-- and tiredly walking.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I don't know where they came from.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they walked into the River San-- because in order to get to Sieniawa, where the ghetto was-- River San-- they had to cross the River San.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the River San didn't have any bridge-- there was only one man who had a small boat, and was taking people one by one.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was intrigued seeing those people, walking, painfully, terribly, terribly distressed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my aunt said, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which meant, oh, those people are Jewish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I say, why?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why should he-- what-- what's that?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she couldn't explain, she just waved her hand-- ha.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, the urge took me to follow them-- and my brother, as well, it was our escape, as well, from-- from our work.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we followed them all the way to the river.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They came to the river, and they were so tired.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They sat there-- because where would you go?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the men-- the-- the gestapo, or the kapos, I don't know, told them to wait for awhile-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were-- they were eating or something.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
